documentation.value:
Calls the given block once for each element.

```ruby
[1, 2, 3].each { |n| puts n }
{ a: 1 }.each { |k, v| puts "#{k}: #{v}" }
```

Returns a new hash containing the contents of self and the other hash. Duplicate keys use values from the other hash.

```ruby
{ a: 1 }.merge({ b: 2 })          # => { a: 1, b: 2 }
{ a: 1 }.merge({ a: 2 })           # => { a: 2 }
{ a: 1 }.merge({ a: 2 }) { |k, v1, v2| v1 + v2 }  # => { a: 3 }
```

Merges the other hash into self, modifying self in place.

```ruby
h = { a: 1 }
h.merge!({ b: 2 })  # h is now { a: 1, b: 2 }
```

Removes the key-value pair and returns the value. Returns `nil` if key not found.

```ruby
h = { a: 1, b: 2 }
h.delete(:a)  # => 1, h is { b: 2 }
```

Deletes every key-value pair for which the block returns truthy.

```ruby
{ a: 1, b: 2, c: 3 }.delete_if { |k, v| v > 1 }
# => { a: 1 }
```

Returns a new hash with values transformed by the block.

```ruby
{ a: 1, b: 2 }.transform_values { |v| v * 2 }
# => { a: 2, b: 4 }
```

Converts the argument to a Hash.

```ruby
Hash(nil)          # => {}
Hash(a: 1, b: 2)   # => { a: 1, b: 2 }
```

